They transport, handle, store or apply manure for a fee.  The company must be licensed annually, and the people who are applicators must be certified annually.    This layer does NOT include confinement site manure applicators, who are essentially private applicators, applying manure from their own confinement feeding operations that have more than 500 animal units, and not charging a fee.</abstract>    <purpose> This digital, geographically referenced data set was developed by the Iowa Department of Natural Resources to carry out agency responsibilities related to management, protection, and development of Iowa's natural resources. </purpose>    <langdata Sync="TRUE">en</langdata></descript>   <timeperd>    <timeinfo>     <sngdate>      <caldate>20110708</caldate>     </sngdate>    </timeinfo>    <current>ground condition</current>   </timeperd>   <status>    <progress>Complete</progress>    <update>Quarterly</update>   </status>   <spdom>    <bounding>     <westbc Sync="TRUE">-98.450270</westbc>     <eastbc Sync="TRUE">-90.078409</eastbc>     <northbc Sync="TRUE">43.553626</northbc>     <southbc Sync="TRUE">0.409868</southbc>    </bounding>    <lboundng><leftbc Sync="TRUE">58784.000000</leftbc><rightbc Sync="TRUE">736136.000000</rightbc><bottombc Sync="TRUE">45412.000000</bottombc><topbc Sync="TRUE">4822297.000000</topbc></lboundng></spdom>   <keywords>    <theme>     <themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Category</themekt>     <themekey>agriculture</themekey><themekey>environment</themekey></theme>    <theme>     <themekt>None</themekt>    </theme>   </keywords>   <accconst>None</accconst>   <useconst> The development of the coverages in the NRGIS Library represents a major investment of staff time and effort.
